3. Blueprint extension path

Blueprints, scripts, applications, data, configuration, and other user-created
payloads that run on TRUEOS through its published runtime interfaces are the
intended and recommended way to extend, customize, automate, and program TRUEOS.

Using Blueprints is permitted, including for commercial purposes. A Blueprint may
change runtime behavior, load code, interact with TRUEOS services, and produce
new behavior inside a running TRUEOS system. That is a legitimate runtime
extension path, not a prohibited modification of the first-party TRUEOS source
code merely because it changes what the system does at runtime.

You own your own Blueprint payloads, subject to whatever rights belong to their
authors and dependencies. This license does not claim ownership of independent
Blueprints that merely use TRUEOS runtime interfaces.

